\lim_{x\to 2}{\frac{2x+4}{x^2-4}} = \lim_{x \to 2}{\frac{2(x+2)}{(x-2)(x+2)}}
 \lim_{x\to 2}{\frac{2}{x-2}}
L.H.L = \lim_{x\to 2^-}{\frac{2}{x-2}} = -\infty
R.H.L = \lim_{x\to2^+}{\frac{2}{x-2}}= +\infty
